2024, you were a year of extremes. You gave me the love of my life and the joy of having my own beautiful home, yet you took away my comfort and left me mentally drained trying to keep up with everything. 

This year I have lost alot of my friendships but I am remain thankful for their time in my life and in parallel universe, we all would still be together. You brought me closer to God and strengthened the bonds of family. Despite moments when giving up felt like the only option, you taught me resilience.

Thank you, 2024, for the lessons, the hardships, and the growth. You were significant in ways I’ll never forget.
